2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the analysis of sorting algorithms and the storage of ordinal data, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses different distortion measures, which are commonly used in machine learning for evaluating the performance of models. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with permutations, which are a fundamental concept in discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the encoding/decoding complexities of code designs, which are relevant to computational complexity.
